We let ${\mathrm{DPic}}(A,B)$ denote the collection of isoclasses of tilting complexes in $D^b(B{\otimes} A^{op})$.  We abuse language a bit and refer to a tilting complex as an object in ${\mathrm{DPic}}(A,B)$.  We let $T^\vee$ denote the dual (a.k.a. quasi-inverse) of an object $T$ in ${\mathrm{DPic}}(A,B)$.  We generally denote the class of a tilting complex $T$ by $[T]$.

